NAME
    UNIVERSAL::to_yaml - to_yaml() method for all objects.

VERSION
    This document describes UNIVERSAL::to_yaml version 0.11

SYNOPSIS
        use UNIVERSAL::to_yaml;
        my $foo = Foo->new();
        print $foo->to_yaml();

DESCRIPTION
    "UNIVERSAL::to_yaml" provide a "to_yaml" method for all objects, by
    defining the method at the special "UNIVERSAL" namespace.

    It effectively calls "YAML::Any::Dump", meaning that the actual backend
    module is upto the selection order from "YAML::Any". See also the
    documentation of YAML::Any for the description.

INTERFACE
    to_yaml()
        This calls "YAML::Any::Dump()" to convert current object to YAML.

DEPENDENCIES
    YAML

BUGS AND LIMITATIONS
    Please report any bugs or feature requests to
    "bug-universal-to_yaml@rt.cpan.org", or through the web interface at
    <http://rt.cpan.org>.

